\begin_layout Section

\lang english
Work Order Structure and Standards
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "app:6.04"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The work order is the method of tracking requests,
 either internally or from external sources,
 such as end-users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A work order should be generated for any task that requires action.
 A work order is not a notification,
 unless it is a notification of an action that needs to occur.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The creation of a work order indicates that a request has been submitted to IT for evaluation.
 It does not guarantee acceptance or execution.
 Work orders are reviewed for scope,
 alignment with IT responsibilities,
 and resource availability.
 If a request is not accepted,
 it will be closed with a clear explanation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A well-crafted work order conveys appropriate information as to the nature and scope of the issue,
 allowing for the IT Department to better assess the situation and provide a resolution.
 It should provide answers to the questions of Who,
 What,
 Where,
 When.
 This will allow the IT Department to determine the Why of the situation,
 and How to resolve it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
By default,
 when a work order comes into the system,
 it will have a status '
\series bold
Queued
\series default
' .
 The ticket should be reviewed to ensure that it has enough information in it:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A clear and informative subject
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A detailed description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A location (Department)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Requested By
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Category
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A ticket that is lacking this information will either need to have the submitter contacted to get more information,
 or the ticket needs to be rejected,
 marked duplicate,
 or marked no response.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Before moving from 'Queued' to Reviewed,
 the ticket should have the submitter added as a watcher to ensure they receive updates about their tickets,
 as well as any related Documentation,
 Assets,
 or Work Orders linked via the ‘Related Issues’ section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Certain fields and functions of the work orders are restricted to IT staff or authenticated internal users.
 These will be noted throughout this appendix.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Subject
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A subject should contain some identifying feature,
 as well as a brief but descriptive explanation of the problem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Good subject:
 RPratt,
 computer emits smoke at 3:23 every afternoon when I spray it with cooking oil.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Bad subject:
 computer broke
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Good subject:
 Justware Says Account is not ActiveApp Person
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Bad subject:
 justware
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
While there are other areas in the work order to document the issue and requester,
 a good subject lets us know at a glance whether the issue needs more immediate attention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Private
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This option is only available to the IT Department or users who are logged into the Work Order System.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This button renders the work order invisible to the general public,
 and only visible to the IT Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This is intended for confidential or private subject matter,
 such as personal contact information,
 passwords,
 or other sensitive information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This is not intended for general issues and should not be marked unless truly a private matter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Please note,
 if the user is not allowed to see Private work orders,
 they will also not receive email updates about the work order even if they are set as a watcher.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A good description of the problem is imperative for the speedy resolution of an problem.
 The more clear the description,
 the less time needs to be spent coaxing more information out of the user to get an understanding of the issue.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
It should contain any relevant error messages,
 affected applications,
 and timestamps.
 In short,
 it should answer:
 What is the issue?
 When is it happening?
 Any existing troubleshooting or descriptive information about the equipment should be listed here.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Subtasks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Only available to the IT Department.
 Used with Project Master work orders to split a large task into smaller tasks,
 such as having a Computer Deployment Master Work Order,
 and then a subtask for each individual computer that gets deployed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Related Issues
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Only available to the IT Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Links to associated Documentation and Assets in our system,
 for tracking what work has been done on which asset and for a standardized method of issue resolution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Status
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Modifying this option is only available to the IT Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All tickets come into the system as "Queued" .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Once the work order is properly reviewed and ready to be worked on,
 the ticket gets moved into 'Reviewed' and a technician can assign their name to it and begin to work on the ticket.
\end_layout

