\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All actions taken during the lifecycle of a work order must be clearly documented in the Notes section.
 Notes should include troubleshooting steps,
 user communications,
 configuration changes,
 and any identified dependencies.
 Thorough documentation ensures continuity across technicians and supports accurate reporting and resolution audits.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Notes may be marked Private if they contain sensitive or internal-use-only information.
 However,
 this should be the exception,
 not the default.
 Private notes are visible only to members of the IT Department.
 Regardless of visibility,
 all notes must be written with the same level of professionalism and discretion as if they were publicly accessible.
\end_layout

